trap, sched, sys/irq: trap & interrupt infrastructure upgrade + BUG-002 fix

sys/scoms, sys/irq: fix IRQ dispatch slot mismatch (BUG-002)
    see BUG_LIST.xml:BUG-002 for more information about behavior and solution.

arch/s390x/trap/ext, sys/timer: route external interrupts through IRQ table
    ext.cxxm handle() now dispatches via irq_dispatch(EXT_*) for every
    external interrupt class instead of using hardcoded fast paths.  timer.cxxm
    registers its handlers through irq_register() like every other subsystem,
    relying on the fixed SCOMS slot allocation above for correct dispatch.

arch/s390x/trap/mcck: MCESA save areas
    Added full MCESA save area layout to arch/s390x/cpu/lowcore_types.cxxm
    (save_area_sync[8], psw_save_area, prefixreg_save_area, fpc, tod, timer,
    clkcomp, last_break, gr, fpr, cr, ar).  dump_mcesa() in mcck.cxxm:90-125
    reports all areas on MCCK.

arch/s390x/trap/mcck: MCIC backlog detection
    Added MCIC_BACKLOG constant (bit 6, 1ULL << 57) to mcck.cxxm.  handle()
    now decodes the MCIC backlog bit and, when a stacked MCCK is detected,
    emits syschk_warning instead of continuing into the regular handler
    path.  Added backlog=15 to the machine_error enum in lib/error.cxxm.

arch/s390x/trap/entry.S: restart handler
    Added trap_restart_entry in entry.S:176-197 with LC_RESTART_DATA /
    LC_RESTART_SOURCE wired into lowcore.  Restarts now trap through a
    dedicated entry rather than falling through the program-check path.

zxfoundation/sched/sched: CPU timer EEVDF accounting
    Implemented EEVDF vruntime accounting in sched.cxxm:502-553 (quantum,
    weight, deadline, need_resched).  cpu_timer_tick() now updates vruntime
    and recalculates deadline instead of only counting ticks.  Timer set
    uses EEVDF_DEFAULT_SLICE for runnable strands and TICK_INTERVAL_TOD for
    the idle strand.

arch/s390x/cpu/sclp: timing alert / service signal
    Service signal path is a null-op pending a future SCLP SCCB reader.
    Acknowledged in code comments as future work — no dispatch regression
    because the vector is not registered.

arch/s390x/trap/pgm: program-check name table
    pgm.cxxm now decodes and reports every PoP §6-4 program-check code by
    name.  Added DXC subclass decoding and TEID inspection for data/page
    exceptions.  arch/s390x/cpu/teid_types.cxxm added to hold the decoded
    TEID bit layout.

lib/uaccess, arch/s390x/trap/pgm: uaccess fixup mechanism
    Added fixup table consulted by pgm.cxxm on access exceptions.
    copy_from_user/copy_to_user now register fixup landing points so that
    a fault on a user access returns -EFAULT to the caller instead of
    escalating to a system check.  Existing uaccess code paths updated to
    emit fixup entries.

zxfoundation/sched/sched, arch/s390x/cpu/ipi: scheduler IPI wiring
    Wired send_reschedule() into enqueue_strand() in sched.cxxm.  When a
    strand is enqueued on a CPU other than the current CPU, the scheduler
    now calls arch.s390x.cpu.ipi.send_reschedule(target_cpu).  This sends
    SIGP external call with EC_SCHEDULE_BIT; the target CPU's handle_ipi
    (smp.cxxm:235) sees the bit and calls sched_resched_current(), dragging
    the CPU out of enabled_wait() to run the woken strand.  Closes the final
    gap in SMP wake-up — remote enqueues no longer require a timer tick to
    be observed by the target.

